# Aegis Health — line-ending policy
#
# Phase 2 ReportReader contract: the Kotlin pipeline output (PreparsedReport
# canonicalized via JsonCanonicalizer.kt per D-06) must byte-match the live
# ground-truth JSONs at eval/fixtures/lab_reports/{vendor}/*-evaluated.json
# AND their mirrored copies at android/app/src/androidTest/assets/lab_reports/.
#
# These files were produced by Python `json.dumps(obj, sort_keys=True,
# indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) + "\n"` on Unix CI/dev machines and ship with
# LF line endings. On Windows with `core.autocrlf=true`, Git would otherwise
# convert them to CRLF on checkout, breaking the byte-identical contract for
# JsonCanonicalizerTest (JVM) and LabReportPipelineFixtureTest (androidTest).
#
# Pin all evaluated-result JSON fixtures and androidTest assets to LF so the
# bytes on every contributor's disk match the bytes the canonicalizer will
# emit, regardless of OS.

# Lab-report ground-truth JSONs (Phase 2 byte-identical contract)
eval/fixtures/lab_reports/**/*-evaluated.json text eol=lf
android/app/src/androidTest/assets/lab_reports/**/*-evaluated.json text eol=lf

# Manifests + license observations near the fixtures stay LF for consistency
eval/fixtures/lab_reports/**/MANIFEST.md text eol=lf
android/app/src/androidTest/assets/lab_reports/**/MANIFEST.md text eol=lf

# PreparsedReport schema + EXTRACTION-SPEC.md are the authoritative spec
# documents these JSONs validate against — keep them LF too.
.planning/specs/PreparsedReport.schema.json text eol=lf

# Phase 3 SAFETY-05 baseline (Plan 03-08): PermissionAuditTest reads this
# file at runtime via androidTest assets and trims each line before
# comparison. The test absorbs lone trailing \r characters, but pinning
# this file to LF keeps the on-disk bytes identical to the bytes the
# audit semantics describe — robust to future test-side changes.
android/app/src/androidTest/assets/permission_baseline.txt text eol=lf

# Phase 4.1 Wave 5 (Plan 04.1-5-01): synthesize_fixture.py emits
# byte-deterministic PDFs that the androidTest pipeline asserts against.
# Mark all PDFs binary so Git's autocrlf=true contributors do NOT rewrite
# lone LF bytes inside the PDF object stream into CRLF on checkout, which
# would corrupt the file and break LabReportSynthesisFixtureTest. Git's
# auto-detection of NUL bytes usually catches this for existing fixtures,
# but the explicit attribute is the correctness guarantee.
*.pdf binary
